  "prompt": "Where can I find device art generators for Samsung S5?",
  "response": "You can find device art generators for the Samsung S5 on several platforms. Here are some options:\n\n1. **Android Device Art Generator by Google**: Google offers an official device art generator that can create images of your app running on various devices, including the Samsung S5. You can find it by searching for \"Android Device Art Generator\" or visiting the official Android developer website.\n\n2. **Mockup Generator Websites**: There are several online mockup generator tools like Placeit, Smartmockups, or Mockup World that allow you to upload your app screenshots and place them on realistic device mockups, including the Samsung S5.\n\n3. **Graphic Design Tools**: Websites like Canva or Adobe Spark may also have mockup templates where you can create device art. Search for free mockups or templates specifically for mobile devices.\n\n4. **Photoshop or GIMP Templates**: If you have graphic design skills, you can find PSD (Photoshop) templates for the Samsung S5 device art on sites like GraphicRiver or Freepik. You can customize them according to your needs.\n\n5. **GitHub Repositories**: Some developers may have created their own device art generators or mockup tools and made them available on GitHub. A search for \"Samsung S5 device mockup\" may yield useful results.\n\nMake sure to check the licensing of any assets you use, especially if you plan to use them for commercial purposes.",
